OL,3,C'Two-tier justice': Why are the
OL,4,Cgovernment and the Sentencing Council
OL,5,Cclashing?
OL,7,FOver the last few weeks, the
OL,8,Fgovernment and the independent body in
OL,9,Fcharge of sentencing have been locked
OL,10,Fin a row over new guidelines that say
OL,11,Fcharacteristics like ethnicity and
OL,12,Fgender should be considered ahead of
OL,13,Fsentencing.
OL,15,FWhen they were set out last month, the
OL,16,Fnew principles from the Sentencing
OL,17,FCouncil immediately sparked
OL,18,Faccusations of "two-tier justice",
OL,19,Fincluding from the Justice Secretary
OL,20,FShabana Mahmood herself.
