OL,3,C'Two-tier justice': Why are the
OL,4,Cgovernment and the Sentencing Council
OL,5,Cclashing?
OL,7,FLast month, the Sentencing Council
OL,8,Freleased new principles for courts to
OL,9,Ffollow when handing out custodial and
OL,10,Fcommunity sentences, including whether
OL,11,Ftime in prison should be suspended.
OL,13,FThe guidance was due to come into
OL,14,Feffect from April 2, and says
OL,15,Fsomething called a 'pre-sentence
OL,16,Freport' would usually be necessary
OL,17,Fbefore sentencing someone from an
OL,18,Fethnic, cultural or faith minority,
OL,19,Falongside other groups such as young
OL,20,Fadults aged 18 to 25, women and
OL,21,Fpregnant women.
